9814],[46.76818,-116.19745],[46.77367,-116.19369],[46.77525,-116.19258],[46.77588,-116.19237],[46.77655,-116.19238],[46.77715,-116.19238],[46.77858,-116.19239],[46.78134,-116.19239],[46.7822,-116.19248],[46.78372,-116.19293],[46.78479,-116.19275],[46.78545,-116.19238],[46.78591,-116.19124],[46.78642,-116.19071],[46.78725,-116.19081],[46.78801,-116.19055],[46.78833,-116.18974],[46.78819,-116.18884],[46.78766,-116.18831],[46.78697,-116.18804],[46.78617,-116.18743],[46.78548,-116.18656],[46.78466,-116.18473],[46.78407,-116.18372],[46.78318,-116.18273],[46.78301,-116.18175],[46.78348,-116.18036],[46.78282,-116.17907]],"routeSource":"OpenStreetMap","routeMiles":54,"pois":[],"gallery":[{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/55/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Bernard_DeVoto_Memorial_Grove_-_NARA_-_7720723.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/55/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Bernard_DeVoto_Memorial_Grove_-_NARA_-_7720723.jpg","cap":"Bernard DeVoto Memorial Grove","desc":"Large trees loom in Bernard DeVoto Memorial Grove. American author and historian Bernard DeVoto, a scholar of the Lewis and Clark Expedition, edited a compilation from the explorers' journals. He found a personal sanctuary in the memorial cedar grove that bears his name--as can you today as you stop along the Northwest Passage Scenic Byway. Location: Idaho (46.509° N 114.790° W) Status: Public dom","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Bernard_DeVoto_Memorial_Grove_-_NARA_-_7720723.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Canoe_Camp%2C_Orofino_-_NARA_-_7720722.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Canoe_Camp%2C_Orofino_-_NARA_-_7720722.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Canoe_Camp%2C_Orofino_-_NARA_-_7720722.jpg","cap":"Canoe Camp, Orofino","desc":"A dugout canoe rests behind an eduational sign at Canoe Camp. While occupied by ancestors of the Nimiipuu for over 4,000 years, this Nez Perce National Historical Park component site is named after the brief stay of the Lewis and Clark Expedition in September-October 1805. Here the explorers, with native assistance, felled Ponderosa pines and constructed dugout canoes for their continued journey t","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Canoe_Camp,_Orofino_-_NARA_-_7720722.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6e/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Kooskia_Crossing-Welcome_Center%2C_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720728.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6e/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Kooskia_Crossing-Welcome_Center%2C_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720728.jpg","cap":"Kooskia Crossing Welcome Center, Kooskia","desc":"Interpretive signs educate the visitor about Kooskia Crossing. This native river crossing was also used as a ford by miners and loggers. Today this gateway marks the split between US Highway 12 and Idaho Highway 13, leading byway travelers to choose their subsequent route: on to Lolo Pass, or south to Grangeville and the Camas Prairie country? Location: Idaho (46.148° N 115.982° W) Status: Public ","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Kooskia_Crossing-Welcome_Center,_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720728.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lenore_Rest_Area_%28Big_Eddy%29%2C_near_Lenore_-_NARA_-_7720729.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lenore_Rest_Area_%28Big_Eddy%29%2C_near_Lenore_-_NARA_-_7720729.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a7/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lenore_Rest_Area_%28Big_Eddy%29%2C_near_Lenore_-_NARA_-_7720729.jpg","cap":"Lenore Rest Area (Big Eddy), near Lenore","desc":"Site of an ancient Nez Perce fishing village, this Idaho Transportation Department rest area is a nice place to stop and imagine life when dugout canoes, not automobiles, transported families along the Clearwater River. Location: Idaho (46.505° N 116.569° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of Nez Perce National Historical Park","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lenore_Rest_Area_(Big_Eddy),_near_Lenore_-_NARA_-_7720729.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lochsa_Historical_Ranger_Station_-_NARA_-_7720730.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lochsa_Historical_Ranger_Station_-_NARA_-_7720730.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/eb/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lochsa_Historical_Ranger_Station_-_NARA_-_7720730.jpg","cap":"Lochsa Historical Ranger Station","desc":"Built in the early 1900s, the historic Lochsa Ranger Station is reminiscent of life at isolated forest service stations during the 1920s and 1930s in the intermountain West. This station is preserved and interpreted today by summer volunteers, who can also provide other information of interest to byway motorists. Location: Idaho (46.147° N 115.596° W) Status: Public domain. Clearwater National For","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Lochsa_Historical_Ranger_Station_-_NARA_-_7720730.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Long_Camp-Riverfront_Park%2C_Kamiah_-_NARA_-_7720727.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Long_Camp-Riverfront_Park%2C_Kamiah_-_NARA_-_7720727.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/34/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Long_Camp-Riverfront_Park%2C_Kamiah_-_NARA_-_7720727.jpg","cap":"Long Camp Riverfront Park, Kamiah","desc":"Leaves change colors at the edge of Long Camp/Riverfront Park. Near the present community of Kamiah, the Lewis and Clark Expedition spent several weeks living among the Nez Perce while awaiting favorable travel conditions over the snowy Bitterroot Range in 1806. Their so-called \"Long Camp\" reinforced the goodwill that existed between the explorers and the Nimiipuu. Location: Idaho (46.218° N 116.0","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Long_Camp-Riverfront_Park,_Kamiah_-_NARA_-_7720727.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Glass_Camp%2C_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720731.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Glass_Camp%2C_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720731.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d7/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Glass_Camp%2C_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720731.jpg","cap":"Looking Glass Camp, Kooskia","desc":"An interpretive sign tells of when US army troops attacked the village of Chief Looking Glass, a peaceful chief who had sought to avoid conflict with the outbreak of the 1877 Nez Perce War. The unprovoked attack drew him and his village into the war, and set the stage for the Nez Perce flight culminating with the Battle of the Bear Paw near Chinook, Montana, where Looking Glass was killed. Locatio","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Looking_Glass_Camp,_Kooskia_-_NARA_-_7720731.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Near_Greer_Ferry%2C_Greer_-_NARA_-_7720725.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Near_Greer_Ferry%2C_Greer_-_NARA_-_7720725.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f7/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Near_Greer_Ferry%2C_Greer_-_NARA_-_7720725.jpg","cap":"Near Greer Ferry, Greer","desc":"The Greer Ferry was a jumping off point for goldseekers heading to Pierce in 1860. The quiet Clearwater River is today a contrast to those turbulent gold rush days. Location: Idaho (46.386° N 116.176° W) Status: Public domain. Idaho Department of Commerce and Labor","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Near_Greer_Ferry,_Greer_-_NARA_-_7720725.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Tipis_near_Nez_Perce_National_Historical_Park_in_Spalding_-_NARA_-_7720733.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Tipis_near_Nez_Perce_National_Historical_Park_in_Spalding_-_NARA_-_7720733.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/de/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Tipis_near_Nez_Perce_National_Historical_Park_in_Spalding_-_NARA_-_7720733.jpg","cap":"Tipis near Nez Perce National Historical Park in Spalding","desc":"Traditional tipis dot the landscape of the Nez Perce Indian Reservation. But don't be fooled: some are intended as visitor lodging. At Nez Perce National Historical Park in Spalding, in summer you can assist park rangers in demonstrating the proper way to pitch a Nez Perce lodge. Location: Idaho (46.209° N 116.006° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of Idaho Department of Commerce and Labor","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_Tipis_near_Nez_Perce_National_Historical_Park_in_Spalding_-_NARA_-_7720733.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_View_of_Dworshak_Dam_from_Canoe_Camp%2C_Orofiino_-_NARA_-_7720724.jpg/1280px-Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_View_of_Dworshak_Dam_from_Canoe_Camp%2C_Orofiino_-_NARA_-_7720724.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/dc/Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_View_of_Dworshak_Dam_from_Canoe_Camp%2C_Orofiino_-_NARA_-_7720724.jpg","cap":"View of Dworshak Dam from Canoe Camp, Orofiino","desc":"This view of Dworshak Dam and the reservoir it created shows many recreational and visitor opportunities. The US Army Corps of Engineers facility, and the separately managed Dworshak National Fish Hatchery--a US Fish Wildlife Service operation--are visible from Canoe Camp, near Orofino. Location: Idaho (46.502° N 116.335° W) Status: Public domain. Nez Perce National Historical Park","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Northwest_Passage_Scenic_Byway_-_View_of_Dworshak_Dam_from_Canoe_Camp,_Orofiino_-_NARA_-_7720724.jpg"}]}